<h2 id="some-facts-about-salt">Some facts about salt</h2>

<p>Among types of sedimentary rock there are the so called <em>evaporites</em>, which formed by precipitation from evaporating saline water. Halite, gypsum, and anhydrite are typical evaporites. Halite is better known as <strong>salt</strong> (one of the rocks that we eat, contributing to shape the worldâ€™s history (<a href="http://www.markkurlansky.com/books/other_non-fiction.aspx">Salt: A World History by Mark Kurlansky</a>.</p>

<p>Evaporites precipitate sequentially, being halite the first to precipitate and, therefore, the dominant mineral in evaporite rock sequences (reference).</p>

